<subSubSection id="D493651613795403FF63FBE072A5E5B9" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9C36369D13795403FF63FBE072A5E5B9" blockId="8.[151,1437,618,1219]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="AEFDEA8F13795403FF63FBE0775DE501" bold="true" box="[199,315,1122,1147]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="5B894D1E13795403FD03FBE17526E501" box="[679,832,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmanica">
<emphasis id="AEFDEA8F13795403FD03FBE17526E501" box="[679,832,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. burmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in coloration and in having the ventral margin of the basal lobe of the aedeagus strongly rounded instead of slightly convex. From 
<taxonomicName id="5B894D1E13795403FB5AFB0573FAE5E4" box="[1278,1436,1159,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Onukia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">
<emphasis id="AEFDEA8F13795403FB5AFB0573FAE5E4" box="[1278,1436,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. assamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5B894D1E13795403FF62FB297738E5B9" box="[198,350,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmanica">
<emphasis id="AEFDEA8F13795403FF62FB297738E5B9" box="[198,350,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. burmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in having the basal pair of quadrate processes on the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
